def audi_filter(df):
    return df[df.manufacturer == "audi"] & (df.model.isin(["a4", "a4 quattro"]))

# Explanation:
The function `audi_filter` takes a DataFrame as input and returns a new DataFrame that contains only the rows with manufacturer "audi" and model being "a4" or "a4 quattro". The function first filters the DataFrame using the bitwise AND operator (`&`) to select the rows where the value in the "manufacturer" column is equal to "audi", then it uses the `isin` method to filter the DataFrame again and return only the rows where the value in the "model" column is either "a4" or "a4 quattro". Finally, the function returns the resulting DataFrame.
